<exercise id="fs-id1163723685297">
<problem id="fs-id1163723685299">
<para id="fs-id1163723685301">A commemorative coin that sells for $40 is advertised to be plated with 15 mg of gold. Suppose gold is worth about $1,300 per ounce. Which of the following best represents the value of the gold in the coin?</para>
<list id="fs-id1163723685306" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha" mark-prefix="(" mark-suffix=")">
<item>$0.33</item>
<item>$0.69</item>
<item>$3.30</item>
<item>$6.90</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1163723685331">
<para id="fs-id1163723685333">The correct answer is (b). There are 28.3 grams per ounce, so  <m:math display="block">
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mtext>mg</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:msup>
  <m:mtext>g</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math>  corresponds to  <m:math display="block">
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mfrac>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo>
     <m:mrow>
      <m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup>
       <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>10</m:mn>
       </m:mrow>
       <m:mrow>
        <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
       </m:mrow>
      </m:msup>
      <m:mtext>g</m:mtext>
     </m:mrow>
    <m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo>
     <m:mrow>
      <m:mn>28.3</m:mn><m:mo> </m:mo><m:mtext>g/oz</m:mtext>
     </m:mrow>
    <m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:mfrac>
  <m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>5.3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:msup>
  <m:mtext>oz</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> . At $1,300 per ounce, the cost of  <m:math display="block">
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mn>5.3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:msup>
  <m:mtext>oz</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math>  is  <m:math display="block">
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>5.3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup>
     <m:mrow>
      <m:mn>10</m:mn>
     </m:mrow>
     <m:mrow>
      <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn>
     </m:mrow>
    </m:msup>
    <m:mtext>oz</m:mtext>
   </m:mrow>
  <m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>$</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>300</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.3em"/><m:mtext>/oz</m:mtext>
   </m:mrow>
  <m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>≅</m:mo><m:mi>$</m:mi><m:mn>0.69</m:mn>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> .</para>
</solution>
</exercise>

